Key Match Events: Nick Castellanos hit a game-winning single in the 11th
Carlos Estévez pitched the 10th and 11th innings, retiring all six batters faced
Spencer Schwellenbach extended the Braves franchise record for consecutive starts allowing three runs or fewer to 21 straight
Post-Match Reflections: Nick Castellanos said the work he does on the field early has helped him become more comfortable taking pitches with two strikes
Carlos Estévez pumped his fists with excitement and received a standing ovation from the sellout crowd
Rob Thomson praised Aaron Nola's performance, noting his improved velocity and command
Miscellaneous Highlights: Orlando Arcia popped out to keep the score tied in the ninth inning
Matt Strahm faced no trouble out of the bullpen for Philadelphia
Whit Merrifield drove in the other Atlanta run by beating out a potential double-play grounder with runners at the corners in the fourth
